contentrichtext.text: {{wiktionarypar|PF|pF}} '''PF''' may refer to: {{TOC right}} == Computer science == * [[Page fault]], a type of exception (error) in computer programming * [[Page file]], a file used as an extension for computer memory * [[PF (firewall)]], OpenBSD's stateful packet filter * [[PF keys]], a type of function keys on old keyboards == Geography == * [[Paracel Islands]], FIPS PUB 10-4 territory code * [[French Polynesia]] (Polynésie française), ISO 3166 internet country code [[.pf]] * PF, registration code on [[Vehicle registration plates of Germany|licence plates]] for [[Pforzheim]] and [[Enzkreis]] district. == Physics == * [[Power factor]], or cos phi, of an AC electric power system * [[Purple fringing]], a type of chromatic aberration in photography * [[Phenol formaldehyde resin]], the earliest synthetic polymer * Picofarad (pF) or petafarad (PF), multiples of [[farad]], the SI unit of electric capacitance (petafarads rarely if ever used) * [[Photon Factory]], a synchrotron located at KEK in Tsukuba, Japan == Organizations == * [[Pheasants Forever]], a non-profit habitat conservation organization * [[Brazilian Federal Police]] (Polícia Federal), in Brazil * [[Patients' Front]], a late 1960s – early 1970s West German pro-illness movement * [[South Vietnamese Popular Force]], a local defense militia formed by South Vietnam during the Vietnam War * [[Patriotic Front (disambiguation)]], name of a political party in several countries == Other uses == * [[Pink Floyd]], an English rock band. * [[Phonetic form]], a level of syntactic representation in linguistics * [[Personal foul (disambiguation)]], a type of foul in several sports * P&F, a [[Point and figure chart]] in the technical analysis of securities * [[Polar front]], in meteorology * Position fix, [[fix (position)]], a position derived from measuring external reference points * [[Power forward (disambiguation)]] * [[Pianoforte]], full original name of the piano instrument * [[Palestinian Airlines]], IATA airline designator * [[Paul Frank]], an artist and fashion designer * [[Pocket Frogs]], a 2010 app for Apple and Android devices * [[Public forum debate]], a debate sanctioned by the National Forensic League * [[Procurator Fiscal]], the public prosecutor in Scotland * [[PF Flyers]], a brand of shoes * [[Project Fanboy]], a comic book news website * [[Provident Fund (disambiguation)]] * [[Pfennig]], a unit of currency formerly used in Germany * [[Plantar fasciitis]], an inflammatory injury in the midfoot * Pilot Flying, in commercial aviation, a designation for the pilot in control of an aircraft; see [[First officer (civil aviation)]] ==See also== * [[PF1 (disambiguation)]] {{disambiguation}}
